Thus, it transpires from the NMR results that the DMA cation is produced via a side reaction (of DMF with HI) and then gets incorporated in the CsPbI3 films. Since only CsI and PbI2 were dissolved in the DMF solvent, the only possible source of DMA in the precursor solution is DMF itself, which is known to slowly hydrolyze to DMA and formic acid (HCOOH)60–65. Addition of HI significantly accelerates the hydrolysis according to Eq. 1, heavily shifting the equilibrium towards the dissociation products, thus generating significant amounts of DMA in the mixture66.1HCON(CH3)2+HI+H2O→(CH3)2NH2I(DMAI)+HCOOH\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
